Conclusions
This review emphasizes large areas of consensus, but also the remaining issues to solve for a complete understanding of dynamin mechanism. We also propose approaches that need to be taken to resolve these issues. Yet, the synthesis of 30 years of work on dynamin allows us to be optimistic, and already, we can state that many aspects of dynamin-mediated membrane fission have been understood. As the prototypic member of a large family of related GTPases that catalyzes both fission and fusion, we hope that the current and future knowledge acquired on the mechanism of dynamin-catalyzed fission will aid our understanding of multiple cellular fission and fusion reactions.
